<div class="text">
  <p>
    When I was in middle school, I began shooting portrait photography with my
    uncle's old <a
      href={"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nikon_D200"}
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      class="text-link">Nikon D200</a
    >. I loved the excuse it gave me to create, and I quickly became obsessed
    with the intersection between technology and art.
  </p>
  <p>
    Nowadays, I'm a recent graduate of the University of Pittsburgh with a
    degree in <a
      href="https://www.sci.pitt.edu/academics/undergraduate-majors/computer-science"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      class="text-link">Computer Science</a
    > and <a
      href="https://www.sci.pitt.edu/academics/undergraduate-majors/digital-narrative-and-interactive-design"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      class="text-link">Digital Narrative and Interactive Design (DNID)</a
    >. I have a passion for designing and building narrative-driven user experiences that feel delightful and
    seamless. I'm always looking for new projects to
    work on when I have the time... (never)
  </p>
  <p>
    Ultimately, I want to create websites that I could see myself using every
    day.
  </p>
